adjudications.original_issue: The canonical description is a slightly abridged version of the comment found in the PDF. The PDF adds a sentence about when the message is output.
adjudications.reasoning: The PDF manual clearly provides additional, relevant information in the 'Comment' section for the UBX-NAV-EOE message, specifically stating when it is output. The canonical description is an abridged version of this comment, lacking the full detail provided in the manual. This is a direct omission of information present in the specified document for the given protocol version.

suggested_fix.change: update the message description to include the full comment from the PDF manual.
suggested_fix.new_value: End of epoch. This message is intended to be used as a marker to collect all navigation messages of an epoch. It is output after all enabled NAV class messages and after all enabled NMEA messages.
